Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.83,0:00:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}The dreams embraced by a single life{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.84,0:00:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}are boundless beyond even the stars.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.84,0:00:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}The dreams that we foster over time{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.85,0:00:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}are waiting for the moment{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}when we come upon them.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.53,0:00:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}The words we exchange{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}make our hearts tremble,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.53,0:00:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}and a chance meeting{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}could change the future.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.21,0:01:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}People, no matter who they are,{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}as they pursue their dreams,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.48,0:01:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}have the courage to travel new paths.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.15,0:01:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}As we leave behind a living{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}testament of our journey,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.49,0:01:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}the Galaxy Railways on which{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}we travel continue ever on.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.18,0:01:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}At some point, a person{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}starts to walk on their own.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.52,0:01:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}They break with the past,{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}and embark on a journey,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.82,0:01:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}where they dream of unlimited{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}futures and possibilities.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.19,0:01:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is Heidel. Advance payment\N{\c&He1e1e1&}transfer has been confirmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.20,0:01:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Things will be carried out\N{\c&He1e1e1&}according to schedule.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.15,0:02:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Tomorrow morning at 1000 hours,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the VIP train {\i1}Dignity No. 125{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.95,0:02:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}will be departing for Planet Farrader.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.82,0:02:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}She will be carrying President Drake,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}of the Republic of the Clarious Cluster.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.83,0:02:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}He's going there to campaign.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.83,0:02:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Each of the platoons takes\N{\c&He1e1e1&}turns handling VIP train duty,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.04,0:02:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and it is Sirius Platoon's\N{\c&He1e1e1&}responsibility this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.84,0:02:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.84,0:02:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yes sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.51,0:02:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Louis!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.84,0:02:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yes sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.18,0:02:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You two will handle this mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.51,0:02:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm sending you both.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.18,0:02:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.52,0:02:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Following the president's\N{\c&He1e1e1&}arrival on Farrader,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.35,0:02:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}his guard will be taken\N{\c&He1e1e1&}over by Vega Platoon,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.52,0:02:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}which will be there\N{\c&He1e1e1&}patrolling the star system.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.86,0:02:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Um, Captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.86,0:02:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hmm? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.19,0:02:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Is there any way I could have\N{\c&He1e1e1&}someone else go in my place?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.53,0:03:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Is there some sort of problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.80,0:03:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No, I just...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.80,0:03:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This isn't like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.47,0:03:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What's the matter, Louis?\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Can't stand being with Yuuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.81,0:03:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I beg your pardon.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I withdraw my request.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.81,0:03:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}VIP train escort duty, tomorrow\N{\c&He1e1e1&}morning at 1000 hours, acknowledged.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.15,0:03:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}"Ties"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.15,0:03:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}President, it's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.82,0:03:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}All right, let them in.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.49,0:03:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Pardon us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.83,0:03:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki Manabu, of the SDF,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Space Defense Force Sirius Platoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.50,0:03:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Louis Fort Drake, likewise.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.84,0:03:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Until we reach Farrader, our mission\N{\c&He1e1e1&}will be to escort the president,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.17,0:03:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}- and oversee {\i1}Dignity's...{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&}- Louis!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.18,0:03:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Why didn't you contact us!?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.85,0:03:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Do you know how worried we were?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.18,0:03:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Stop that. The young lady is on duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.52,0:03:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Honey, you don't have\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to take that tone!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.52,0:03:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I am terribly sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.19,0:04:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}So much for formal greetings.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}To be frank,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.46,0:04:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I don't expect anything from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.13,0:04:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Your jurisdiction is, after all,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}limited to the space rails.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.77,0:04:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I won't actually be exposed to danger\N{\c&He1e1e1&}until after I get off the train.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.14,0:04:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You are quite right. However...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.48,0:04:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You see? These latest-model\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Cyborg SPs guard me full-time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.82,0:04:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Naturally, they're with me
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.12,0:04:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}when I travel from world\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to world like this, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.82,0:04:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If, by some chance,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}something does happen,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.56,0:04:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I won't be needing\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to ask for your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.83,0:04:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Think of this as a vacation,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}and enjoy the trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.56,0:04:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Why didn't you say anything about\N{\c&He1e1e1&}your father being the president?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.23,0:04:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Was there any need?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.57,0:04:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Now that you mention it...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.24,0:04:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If saying so would have gotten me out\N{\c&He1e1e1&}of this duty, I would have liked to...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.24,0:05:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What's the story here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.24,0:05:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}All he ever worries\N{\c&He1e1e1&}about is how he appears,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.31,0:05:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and he interferes in everything.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}He's a terrible father.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.85,0:05:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The school I went to...\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the friends I kept...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.52,0:05:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and even who I would marry\N{\c&He1e1e1&}was arranged by him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.52,0:05:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I couldn't stand having a father like\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that any more, and I ran away from home.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.86,0:05:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I even chose this job
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.76,0:05:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}because I didn't want to follow\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the path that he had settled on for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.54,0:05:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's sort of the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}opposite of you, huh {\i1}Yuuki-kun?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.88,0:05:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}- Louis!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}- Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.54,0:05:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm so surprised to see you, Louis!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.21,0:05:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm sorry, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.22,0:05:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Thank goodness you're looking well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.89,0:05:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm so relieved.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.89,0:05:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}But the SDF, of all things...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.72,0:05:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Why would you choose\N{\c&He1e1e1&}such a dangerous job?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.56,0:05:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's okay. Mom, you're the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}same as ever, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.17,0:06:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}As you can see,\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Dignity{\i0} here is the latest model,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.81,0:06:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and the engine room is fully automated,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}so there are no problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.18,0:06:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Just what you'd expect of a VIP train.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.51,0:06:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}And that VIP has his own Cyborg SPs,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}which means there's nothing for us to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.19,0:06:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I suppose not.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.52,0:06:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Well, let's both take it easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.86,0:06:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Louis, I think your father\N{\c&He1e1e1&}really was happy to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.87,0:06:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Ridiculous. The expression on\N{\c&He1e1e1&}his face never even changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.21,0:06:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It was like he wanted nothing\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to do with his disowned daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.55,0:06:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You know, Louis, your father has\N{\c&He1e1e1&}a very important speech coming up...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.22,0:06:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}His speech will consist\N{\c&He1e1e1&}of reading the text
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.05,0:06:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}that someone else has\N{\c&He1e1e1&}written for him, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.56,0:06:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}He hasn't changed at all.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Neither has his disdainful attitude,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.46,0:06:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}or the egotistical way he thinks\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that only he is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.16,0:07:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Louis...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.86,0:07:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.53,0:07:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Pardon me. Here is the text\N{\c&He1e1e1&}for your speech on Farrader.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.54,0:07:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's felt that this is as far as\N{\c&He1e1e1&}we should press things right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.22,0:08:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I hear that your daughter has\N{\c&He1e1e1&}become an SDF platoon member.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.49,0:08:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}So it would seem.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.16,0:08:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Would you like to have lunch together?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.83,0:08:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}With my daughter?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.17,0:08:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yes, shall I invite her?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.17,0:08:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'd sooner have you invite\N{\c&He1e1e1&}a terrorist leader.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.84,0:08:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Listen, Louis, just talk\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to your father once more.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.18,0:08:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Where have you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.85,0:08:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I went to the lead car to\N{\c&He1e1e1&}say hello to the conductor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.85,0:08:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'll go too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.19,0:08:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Er, {\i1}Yuuki-san,{\i0} was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.19,0:08:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yes. Yuuki Manabu.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.19,0:08:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Are you just one of Louis' co-workers?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.53,0:08:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I mean, by any chance, are you\N{\c&He1e1e1&}seeing each other, or anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.53,0:08:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.87,0:08:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}H- hold on! What are you\N{\c&He1e1e1&}talking about, Mom!?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.87,0:08:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The president!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.88,0:08:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Get out of here, Chris!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.21,0:08:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.82,0:09:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Why are the Cyborg SPs?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.49,0:09:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}President...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.49,0:09:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Chris!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.50,0:09:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}- Are you all right?\N{\c&He1e1e1&}- Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.83,0:09:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}President!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.51,0:09:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Louis! Honey, are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.85,0:09:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.85,0:09:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Thank goodness!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.19,0:09:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What happened!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.86,0:09:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The Cyborg SPs attacked the president.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.86,0:09:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}They're still moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.53,0:09:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Louis, the forward car!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.87,0:09:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.53,0:09:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.20,0:09:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.20,0:09:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Yuuki-kun!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.54,0:09:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Louis, close the door and lock it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.88,0:10:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Louis, where's {\i1}Yuuki-san!?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.88,0:10:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Our mission is to protect the president.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.92,0:10:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Yuuki-kun,{\i0} what are you planning to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.87,0:11:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}All right...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.56,0:11:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Conductor, please lower the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}rail shields for 10 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.90,0:11:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Y- you're not serious!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}The rail shields?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.57,0:11:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Just do it, quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.24,0:11:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.92,0:11:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}All right, bring the shields back!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.58,0:11:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.92,0:11:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We're okay now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.92,0:11:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Thank goodness!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.59,0:11:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Amazing, {\i1}Yuuki-kun.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.26,0:12:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Slow to 80%.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Reduce speed and couple up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.87,0:12:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.54,0:12:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I can't believe this is happening...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.21,0:12:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Yuuki-kun!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.56,0:12:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Louis!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.89,0:12:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Speed 170. Decelerate briefly by 20%.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.90,0:12:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Louis!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.57,0:12:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Louis!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.25,0:12:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Your wife has taken a sedative,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}and is resting now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.92,0:12:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.92,0:13:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Actually, about the text\N{\c&He1e1e1&}of your speech...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.53,0:13:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I don't have another copy of it,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}so I will get started on it again now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.20,0:13:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No, just keep this under your hat.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.53,0:13:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This gives me a good excuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.54,0:13:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's all right.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I've got my text right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.87,0:13:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}President...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.21,0:13:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You must be tired. Get some rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.21,0:13:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.55,0:13:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You still take it without sugar, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.22,0:13:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.90,0:13:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is Yuuki aboard {\i1}Dignity.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.23,0:13:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What happened? Maintain regular contact.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.57,0:13:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You probably already\N{\c&He1e1e1&}heard from Headquarters...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.91,0:13:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No, we haven't heard anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.58,0:13:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's odd. The conductor\N{\c&He1e1e1&}should have contacted them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.52,0:14:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What's going on out there, Yuuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.19,0:14:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Right. A little while ago,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the president's...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.19,0:14:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki! What's wrong, Yuuki!?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.86,0:14:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}W- why, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.53,0:14:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Are you all right? Yuuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.86,0:14:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Damn, I have to take\N{\c&He1e1e1&}care of this, fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.87,0:14:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}System check!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.87,0:14:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}System check, standby.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.54,0:14:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Orbital communications radar\N{\c&He1e1e1&}reading normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.21,0:14:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Big One{\i0} moving to launch position.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.21,0:14:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Ascent Float lock confirmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.22,0:14:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Gravitational barrier\N{\c&He1e1e1&}generator systems normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.88,0:14:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Energy normal. Pressure within the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}boiler is rising. Cylinder valves open.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.89,0:14:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Engage main circuits.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.23,0:14:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Engaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.56,0:14:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Systems all green!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.23,0:14:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Big One,{\i0} move out!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.52,0:15:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I offer my gratitude for saving me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.53,0:15:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Looks like you've been favored\N{\c&He1e1e1&}with a good friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.86,0:15:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's not as though I don't understand\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the reasons why you took off into space,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.20,0:15:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}but why would you choose\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to work for the SDF?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.20,0:15:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If you chose this path out of some\N{\c&He1e1e1&}haphazard desire to rebel against me,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.88,0:15:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}then you dishonor the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Galaxy Railways and its passengers,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.51,0:15:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}the ones you are\N{\c&He1e1e1&}supposed to be protecting.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.55,0:15:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's not so!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.89,0:15:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Yuuki-san{\i0} is asking for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.55,0:15:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}He said he wanted you to\N{\c&He1e1e1&}come at once for some reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.56,0:15:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Okay, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.89,0:15:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I wonder what the matter is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.56,0:15:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'll be back soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.56,0:15:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Conductor, take care of things here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.90,0:15:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}As you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.23,0:15:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Has something happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.90,0:16:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No, there's no problem.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Please do not be alarmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.84,0:16:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}In that case, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.51,0:16:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Yuuki-kun{\i0} could have come himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.51,0:16:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}The conductor just now...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.52,0:16:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It couldn't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.19,0:16:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Get down!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.19,0:16:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.19,0:16:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Die!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.53,0:16:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.87,0:16:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.87,0:16:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Damn you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.21,0:16:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Too bad! How about I blast a hole through\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that delicate little body of yours!?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.55,0:16:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}President Drake, there are\N{\c&He1e1e1&}those who will not be served
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.69,0:16:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}by the new policies\N{\c&He1e1e1&}you're going to announce.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.89,0:16:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If I fail, they're planning\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to blow the whole train up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.56,0:17:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's no use trying to shield him,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}young lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.50,0:17:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I won't let you kill the president!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.50,0:17:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I admire your sense of duty, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.84,0:17:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's the SDF! You're through!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.18,0:17:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.85,0:17:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I've got to go through with this!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.51,0:17:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Run!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.18,0:17:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Louis!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.19,0:17:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If I can just kill the president...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.52,0:17:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Even if you did, you'd be arrested!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}And so will the mastermind behind this!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.19,0:17:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.86,0:17:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Dignity,{\i0} come in!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Is the president okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.53,0:17:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is the SDF, Vega Platoon! {\i1}Dignity!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.87,0:17:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The president!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.87,0:17:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's no use, they're not responding.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.20,0:17:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Don't let that ship get away!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.55,0:18:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Dignity{\i0} is all right, but I can't tell\N{\c&He1e1e1&}what the situation is inside her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.83,0:18:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}All right, come alongside.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}We'll link up and board her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.50,0:18:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You should give up now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.50,0:18:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Be quiet!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.17,0:18:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Louis!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.50,0:18:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.18,0:18:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's far enough, Conductor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.18,0:18:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Whoa! Would you mind holding up?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.52,0:18:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Walking out on the job, Conductor?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.52,0:18:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.19,0:18:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Is the president okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.52,0:18:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.19,0:18:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}President!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.53,0:18:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's just a scratch.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.19,0:18:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm terribly sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.20,0:18:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Don't worry about it. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.20,0:18:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's all right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.87,0:18:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}My foolish daughter...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.83,0:19:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}War is something that brings\N{\c&He1e1e1&}pain to many people,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.13,0:19:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and gives rise to nothing\N{\c&He1e1e1&}but sadness and hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.17,0:19:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Today, I hereby make this declaration:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.84,0:19:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The Republic of the Clarious Cluster
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.74,0:19:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}will prohibit itself from using force\N{\c&He1e1e1&}as a means of foreign policy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.85,0:19:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What's he talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.18,0:19:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Damn...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.19,0:19:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Those who resort to using an unreasonable\N{\c&He1e1e1&}amount of force will not be tolerated.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.86,0:19:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Further, the use of force to\N{\c&He1e1e1&}control others against their will
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.43,0:19:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}is that much more unpardonable.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.87,0:19:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I promise the withdrawal from Ludaile,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}which has been a long-pending problem,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.87,0:20:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}as well as a reduction in the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}military budget, and a reduction...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.54,0:20:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}...or a removal of\N{\c&He1e1e1&}military facilities...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.88,0:20:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}...from 16 of the Republic's 19 worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.22,0:20:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I would like to take the first steps\N{\c&He1e1e1&}toward establishing real justice together.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.22,0:20:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.57,0:20:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You're your father's daughter,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.24,0:20:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I don't know what difficulties\N{\c&He1e1e1&}you have between you,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.91,0:20:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}but what your father is trying to do...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.92,0:20:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}...goes along with the job\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that you and I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.26,0:20:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You said that you and I were opposites,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.26,0:20:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}but we could be more alike\N{\c&He1e1e1&}than you'd expect, huh?
